<section class="about" id="about">
  <div class="about-label">About</div>

  <div class="about-body">
    <p>
      I'm a visual designer who also writes code. I spend most of my time in Figma exploring
      editorial aesthetics, typography, and grid systems. While design is my primary focus, I
      like being the one to code it—usually reaching for Astro, React, or Vue, and
      occasionally falling down a backend rabbit hole just to see how the data connects.
    </p>
    <p>
      When I'm not doing client work, I'm usually setting random design challenges for
      myself, poking around AI tools, or leaving half-baked UI concepts in my notes.
    </p>
    <p>
      My path here wasn't a straight line. I spent a decade in customer experience for major
      publications like Tribune Publishing and the Los Angeles Times. Eventually, I made the
      pivot—doing front-end at MC2, then visual design for AI training models at Wirestock.
      It's a different world now, but the instinct is exactly the same: caring about how
      things look, feel, and work for real people.
    </p>
  </div>
</section>